The members of the Exodus company dispersed. They were part of the second assault division, second army. Initially, they were separated into two distinct companies, Cohort and Dragger, before being reunited. This was a splinter company, and Cohren didn't know what to think about his promotion to first lieutenant, mainly due to the reasons behind it.
Cohren and Nemic, the leader of the first platoon, marched together under the light of the numerous operational forward base lighting fixtures, powered by generators. Most were tinted red to conceal them from enemy bombers. Daybreak had resorted to both air and ground Wild Weasel assaults to combat them.
"New day, new mission for the pioneers of hell," began Nemic with a dry laugh. "Where are they sending us?"
"A forward operational base outside Ianlos. We were sent to support the ground assault," Cohren replied, pulling on his cigarette. A part of him blamed Craith for initiating him with tobacco, but a year of combat changes a man, and he fell silent.
"Bloody hell. The situation is getting worse on the front," muttered Nemic. "All the news coming from there is 'Contribute to the war effort. Send aid to the Kurgan front.' Why not send aid to the Howland front?"
"Amen, my brother," said Cohren as he flicked his cigarette into the mud. "Anyhow, we're going with the first armored platoon, so we won't have to walk. Captain Shaw should be here."
"Shaw gave us a ride,?" asked Nemic, a little surprised.
"Yep. Honestly, he's not as bad as I thought. I mean, he's not exceptional, but he's not unbearable."
Cohen placed his thumb and index finger on his throat mic while adjusting his backpack. "To all units of Exodus Company, assemble at the west vehicle park once you have finished. We depart with the first armored platoon at 5:00."
Every few seconds, he received responses from squadron commanders. Haris, Craith, and Ravik were all low-ranking non-commissioned officers when they arrived here. The four of them had been very good friends since their initial training on Earth. It seemed so long ago, even though it couldn't be more than two years. They had then been squadron commanders. But Craith now commanded the second platoon since last week, after the previous commander, who had been wounded by a Daybreak sharpshooter, was demobilized.
As they walked toward the vehicle park, Cohren and Nemic saw a group of about eight main combat tanks marked Kronos and four Strykers. Their crews were busy, making sure their war machines were ready for departure. Cohren quickly spotted Captain Boradin Shaw, who was talking with the commander of the armored platoon. As they approached, Shaw turned and walked towards them, his usually cold face showing no emotion.
"Lieutenant Nemic... Lieutenant Valturi..." He said that Cohren was slower, looking at Cohren's pistol holster before looking at them again. "I suppose the company is ready."
